b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av164.htm)  [Next](av166.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 79. Charm for procuring increase of grain.\n\n1\\. May this bounteous Nabhasaspati (the lord of the cloud) preserve for us\n(possessions) without measure in our house!  \n2\\. Do thou, O Nabhasaspati, keep strengthening food in our house, may\nprosperity and goods come hither!  \n3\\. O bounteous god, thou dost command thousandfold prosperity: of that do\nthou bestow upon iis, of that do thou give us, in that may we share with thee!\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VI, 50. Exorcism of vermin infesting grain in the field](av166.htm)\n\n'